quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  27,23,"I found a woman ruling over them, she has been given all things, and she has a great throne"
  27,24,"I found her and her people worshipping the sun instead of Allah, and Shaytan has made their deeds fair seeming to them to prevent them from the way, so they have no guidance"
  27,25,"So they do not prostrate themselves before Allah, Who brings to light what is hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knows what you conceal and what you reveal"
  27,26,"Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa, the Lord of the Supreme Throne"
  27,27,"(Sulayman) said: \"We shall see whether you speak the truth or you are (one) of the liars"
  27,28,"Go you with this letter of mine and deliver it to them, then draw back from them and see what they return"
  27,29,"She said: \"O chiefs! Verily, here is delivered to me a noble letter"
  27,30,"Verily, it is from Sulayman, and it (reads): `In the Name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful"
  27,31,"Be you not exalted against me, but come to me submitting (as Muslims)"
  27,32,"She said: \"O chiefs! Advise me in case of mine. I decide no case till you are present with me"
  27,33,"They said: \"We have great strength, and great ability for war, but it is for you to command; so think over what you will command"
  27,34,"She said: \"Verily, kings, when they enter a town, they destroy it and make the most honorable among its people the lowest. And thus they do"
  27,35,"But verily, I am going to send him a present, and see with what (answer) the messengers return"